# Solutions to Questions based on grep command


1. Write a Pattern to Match only Directory.
>> ls -lrt | grep -E "^d"

2. Write a Pattern to Match only files.
>> ls -lrt | grep -E "^-"

3. Find the Servers ipv4 info from a file.
>> grep -Ew "[0-9]{3}\.[0-9]{3}\.[0-9]{3}\.[0-9]{3}" ip.txt			
>> grep -E "\b[0-9]{3}\.[0-9]{3}\.[0-9]{3}\.[0-9]{3}\b" ip.txt
